        rationale: "BNP <100 pg/mL has a negative predictive value >95% for heart failure. A BNP of 52 pg/mL strongly suggests that acute dyspnea is NOT caused by heart failure. The NP should investigate non-cardiac etiologies such as COPD exacerbation, pulmonary embolism, pneumonia, or asthma. While BNP does not diagnose a specific pulmonary condition, it effectively excludes HF."
